The Internet Archive, founded by Brewster Kahle in 1996, is dedicated to maintaining an archive of the Internet. Their collections include snapshots of the World Wide Web and Usenet. The Archive also maintains 'The Wayback Machine' which, given a URL, allows the user to see versions of the corresponding web page over time. Examples of the Wayback Machine's archives: Amazon, Microsoft and the BBC. The Archive's total collection, as of 2003, is around 100 terabytes of data. External link The Internet Archive
